DTSTAMP:20260710T043905Z
UID:occ-1368@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:The 1993 Robin Williams film as a Broadway musical: divorced d
 ad\, Scottish nanny disguise\, national touring production.\n\nThe musical
  adaptation of the 1993 film: Daniel Hillard\, an out-of-work actor who lo
 ses custody of his kids in a messy divorce\, invents Euphegenia Doubtfire\
 , a kindly Scottish nanny\, to stay in their lives. Songs come from Wayne 
 and Karey Kirkpatrick\, the songwriting team behind Something Rotten!\, wi
 th Karey Kirkpatrick and John O'Farrell sharing book duties. Four-time Ton
 y winner Jerry Zaks directs. A national touring production\, presented as 
 part of the Broadway in Atlanta series.
GEO:33.7726136;-84.3853395
LAST-MODIFIED:20260710T043457Z
LOCATION:Fox Theatre\, 660 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://foxtheatre.evenue.net/cgi-bin/ncommerce3/SEGetGroupList?groupC
 ode=MRS&linkID=fta&shopperContext=&caller=&appCode=
END:VEVENT
