BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Beetlejuice
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270611T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270611T220000
DTSTAMP:20260710T043905Z
UID:occ-1750@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:The musical of Tim Burton's 1988 film: a grieving teen\, two h
 apless ghosts\, and a demon summoned by name.\n\nThe Broadway musical base
 d on Tim Burton's 1988 film\, with songs by Eddie Perfect and a book by Sc
 ott Brown and Anthony King. Lydia Deetz\, a teenager mourning her mother a
 nd ignored by her father\, moves into a house haunted by a recently deceas
 ed couple and a striped-suit demon who turns visible only if the living sa
 y his name three times. New York magazine's critic called it 'loud\, cheek
 y\, and all about excess\,' true to its source. Expect 'Day-O' at the dinn
 er party.
GEO:33.7726136;-84.3853395
LAST-MODIFIED:20260710T043457Z
LOCATION:Fox Theatre\, 660 Peachtree St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://foxtheatre.evenue.net/cgi-bin/ncommerce3/SEGetGroupList?groupC
 ode=BEE&linkID=fta&shopperContext=&caller=&appCode=
END:VEVENT
