BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Operation Mincemeat
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270706T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270706T220000
DTSTAMP:20260710T043905Z
UID:occ-1755@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Musical Theatre
DESCRIPTION:SpitLip's Olivier-winning musical comedy about the real WWII s
 cheme that fooled Hitler with a corpse and forged papers.\n\nThe true stor
 y from 1943: British intelligence dressed a dead body as a fictitious Roya
 l Marines major\, planted fake invasion plans in his briefcase\, and float
 ed him off the coast of Spain to draw Nazi troops away from Sicily. Ian Fl
 eming\, not yet the inventor of James Bond\, is among the schemers. The mu
 sical comedy comes from SpitLip\, the four-person British troupe who wrote
